  "prompt": "What is cognition?",
  "response": "Cognition is the mental process of acquiring knowledge and understanding through thought, experience, and the senses. It involves various mental activities such as:\n\n1. Perception - interpreting sensory information\n2. Attention - focusing on specific stimuli\n3. Memory - storing and retrieving information\n4. Reasoning - thinking logically and solving problems\n5. Learning - acquiring new knowledge or skills\n6. Decision-making - choosing between alternatives\n7. Language processing - understanding and communicating\n8. Problem-solving - finding solutions to challenges\n\nCognition helps humans interpret the world, process information, and respond to different situations. It is studied across multiple disciplines, including psychology, neuroscience, and cognitive science.",
